      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>A Massachusetts legislator wants to revise marriage license applications to include a warning that abusing one's spouse is a crime.</p>
        <p>"Neither you nor your spouse is the property of the other," says the warning  drafted by State Representative Barbara Gray, Democrat of Framingham.</p>
        <p>Ms. Gray said yesterday that the warning was a way to tell "couples with stars in their eyes and bliss in their hearts that one out of two relationships  have an element of abuse in them, and that's something they should consider before they get married."</p>
      </block>
